e considered a rogue/monk combo, due to using special moves for h2h skills, defenseive skills(such as innate dodge, caused by godly natural agility of vamps) and small piercers such as rogues do.<br><br>I'm also no game designer, so these traits are very loose and undefined.  But i just wanted to hear what everyone else had to say on the topic of introducing vampires as a new class maybe in an upcoming EQ expansion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udalthor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalthor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 1:11:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2289.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vampires in Eq</span><hr size=1> I see a problem here.<br><br>If VI decided to make vampires part of this game, and water is NOT good for them, VI would put most of their epic drops in Kedge Keep and Lake Rathetear.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uvorex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vore X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 1:14:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2289.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.guildwar.org/~zelse/images/vegeta_c.gif WIDTH=6